The paper deals with Markov chain Monte Carlo methods, which are commonly used in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The focus is on the Restricted/Deep Boltzmann Machine, which is a popular model in deep learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves information theory (cs.IT) and neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper discusses the implementation of the Gibbs sampler, which is a common technique in statistical inference (cs.SI). Finally, the paper involves theoretical analysis of a practical implementation, which could fall under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
